        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 12:53PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1250 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Richfield, Albemarle, and Oakboro. These storms
were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could damage trees and blow around unsecured
objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Badin Lake, Plyler, Badin, Richfield, New London,
Pinehaven Marina, Eldorado, Fish Tales Marina, and Morrow Mountain
State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning can be expected with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
